<p>Linalg is a <strong>linear algebra and game math library</strong> for Lean 4, providing vectors,
matrices, quaternions, and geometric primitives optimized for 2D and 3D game programming.</p>

<h3>Key Features</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Vectors</strong> - Vec2, Vec3, Vec4 with full algebra (add, sub, scale, dot, cross, normalize, lerp)</li>
  <li><strong>Matrices</strong> - Mat2, Mat3, Mat4 in column-major order (GPU-compatible)</li>
  <li><strong>Quaternions</strong> - Rotation representation with slerp interpolation, gimbal-lock free</li>
  <li><strong>Geometry</strong> - Ray, AABB, Sphere, Plane, Triangle, OBB, Capsule, Frustum primitives</li>
  <li><strong>Intersections</strong> - Ray casting, primitive-vs-primitive tests, frustum culling, 2D collision (SAT, GJK)</li>
  <li><strong>Animation</strong> - Easing functions, spring physics, smooth damping</li>
  <li><strong>Curves</strong> - Bezier curves, Catmull-Rom splines, arc-length parameterization</li>
  <li><strong>Noise</strong> - Perlin, Simplex, FBM, ridged, turbulence, Worley noise</li>
  <li><strong>Spatial Structures</strong> - BVH, Octree, Quadtree, KD-Tree for efficient queries</li>
  <li><strong>Physics</strong> - Particle simulation, rigid body dynamics, collision response</li>
</ul>

